    <header>
        <h1>Welcome to the World of Fruits!</h1>
        <p>Discover different types of fruits and learn more about them.</p>
    </header>

    <section>
        <h2>Fruits Collection</h2>

        <!-- Fruit 1: Apple -->
        <article>
            <h3>Apple</h3>
            <p><strong>Scientific Name:</strong> Malus domestica</p>
            <p><strong>Description:</strong> Apples are a popular fruit known for their sweet taste and crunchy texture. They come in various colors, including red, green, and yellow.</p>
            <p><strong>Health Benefits:</strong> Apples are high in fiber and Vitamin C, promoting good digestion and boosting the immune system.</p>
        </article>

        <!-- Fruit 2: Banana -->
        <article>
            <h3>Banana</h3>
            <p><strong>Scientific Name:</strong> Musa</p>
            <p><strong>Description:</strong> Bananas are a tropical fruit that are soft and sweet with a yellow peel. They are one of the most consumed fruits globally.</p>
            <p><strong>Health Benefits:</strong> Bananas are rich in potassium and are great for heart health and muscle function.</p>
        </article>

        <!-- Fruit 3: Orange -->
        <article>
            <h3>Orange</h3>
            <p><strong>Scientific Name:</strong> Citrus sinensis</p>
            <p><strong>Description:</strong> Oranges are citrus fruits known for their refreshing, tangy taste and high juice content.</p>
            <p><strong>Health Benefits:</strong> Oranges are an excellent source of Vitamin C, which is essential for skin health and immune support.</p>
        </article>

        <!-- Fruit 4: Mango -->
        <article>
            <h3>Mango</h3>
            <p><strong>Scientific Name:</strong> Mangifera indica</p>
            <p><strong>Description:</strong> Mangoes are tropical fruits with a sweet, juicy flesh and a large pit. They are known for their distinct flavor and are often called the "king of fruits."</p>
            <p><strong>Health Benefits:</strong> Mangoes are packed with Vitamin A and antioxidants, which help maintain healthy skin and improve vision.</p>
        </article>

        <!-- Fruit 5: Grapes -->
        <article>
            <h3>Grapes</h3>
            <p><strong>Scientific Name:</strong> Vitis vinifera</p>
            <p><strong>Description:</strong> Grapes are small, round fruits that can be red, green, or purple. They grow in clusters and are often used to make wine.</p>
            <p><strong>Health Benefits:</strong> Grapes are rich in antioxidants and have heart-protective properties.</p>
        </article>

        <!-- Fruit 6: Pineapple -->
        <article>
            <h3>Pineapple</h3>
            <p><strong>Scientific Name:</strong> Ananas comosus</p>
            <p><strong>Description:</strong> Pineapples are tropical fruits with a tough, spiky outer skin and sweet, tangy flesh.</p>
            <p><strong>Health Benefits:</strong> Pineapples are high in Vitamin C and bromelain, an enzyme known for its anti-inflammatory properties.</p>
        </article>
    </section>

